	     Rabat - A runaway Moroccan passenger train travelled for 1.5km without its driver who had gone for a coffee, reports said on Tuesday. Monday's incident happened when the driver of the Rabat-bound train got off at Kenitra station about 40km northeast of the capital, the Al-Massae daily said. The train, with 20 people on board, started rolling in the wrong direction before later coming to a halt on its own. Nobody on board the locomotive was hurt. The National Railways Office said an investigation was under way into the circumstances. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  